Sentencas: Tailoring the properties of cathode is of great importance to improve the performance of proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells (SOFC-H).
Titulo: Modification of electrocatalytic activity of BaCe0.40Sm0.20Fe0.40O3-δ with Co3O4 as cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: This work demonstrates that the performance of BaCe0.40Sm0.20Fe0.40O3-delta cathode can be optimized by introducing appropriate amount of Co3O4.
Titulo: Modification of electrocatalytic activity of BaCe0.40Sm0.20Fe0.40O3-δ with Co3O4 as cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The 5-10 wt% Co3O4 reacts with BaCe0.40Sm0.20Fe0.40O3-delta, forming conductive mixed oxygen ionic-electronic phases.
Titulo: Modification of electrocatalytic activity of BaCe0.40Sm0.20Fe0.40O3-δ with Co3O4 as cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The materials with 5-10 wt% Co3O4 exhibits protonic and improved oxygen ionic-electronic conductivity in wet air, which contributes greatly to the electrocatalytic activity toward the reaction on the cathode.
Titulo: Modification of electrocatalytic activity of BaCe0.40Sm0.20Fe0.40O3-δ with Co3O4 as cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cell
Modification of electrocatalytic activity of BaCe0.40Sm0.20Fe0.40O3-δ with Co3O4 as cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Co3O4 demonstrates lower ASR, lower cathode overpotential, higher exchange current density, and higher peak power density.
Titulo: Modification of electrocatalytic activity of BaCe0.40Sm0.20Fe0.40O3-δ with Co3O4 as cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Higher content of Co3O4 (20%) will result in the disappearance of protonic conducting phase and denser electrode microstructure, which are detrimental to the performance.
Titulo: Modification of electrocatalytic activity of BaCe0.40Sm0.20Fe0.40O3-δ with Co3O4 as cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: This work demonstrates that designing cathode materials with modified microstructure, which is simultaneously protonic, oxygen ionic and electronic conductive, is crucial to improve the performance of SOFC-H. (C) 2013
Titulo: Modification of electrocatalytic activity of BaCe0.40Sm0.20Fe0.40O3-δ with Co3O4 as cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cell
